Title: ORTHOGONALIZATION-BASED ITERATIVE SOLVERS FOR GENERALIZED STOKES PROBLEMS  
Author: R. BRAMLEY, X. WANG and D. PELLETIER 
Abstract: Two methods for solving the generalized Stokes problems that occur in viscous, incompressible flows are described and tested. Both are based on some type of linear algebraic orthogonaliza-tion process. The first, EMGS, is a preconditioner derived from an incomplete Gram-Schmidt factorization, and it is proven to exist whenever the matrix being preconditioned can be factored using Gaussian elimination. For M-matrices, EMGS is proven to give a better approximate factorization than ILU preconditioning, but this requires a large amount of intermediate storage for computing the preconditioner. The second orthogonalization approach gives a derived system which eliminates the indefiniteness of the generalized Stokes problem, and keeps the velocity field in the space of discrete null-divergence vectors. Both methods are tested on problems extracted from a finite element fluid flow solver. 
